message.content: cs.IT, cs.IT is the most likely category as the paper deals with information theory and entropy. Other possible categories could be cs.DS (discrete mathematics) as the paper discusses properties of measure spaces, cs.MS (mathematical physics) as the paper mentions applications in statistical physics, cs.NA (numerical analysis) as the paper establishes the existence of projections onto convex and certain closed sets, and cs.CG (computational geometry) as the paper discusses geometric properties of relative entropies.
